& [SourceSet] is the bounded source frame
  + [source_001] is Barker and Prange, Scale-invariant estimates and vorticity alignment for Navier-Stokes in the half-space with no-slip boundary conditions
    = link: https://arxiv.org/abs/1906.08225
    = use: vorticity-direction uniform continuity can rule out singularity under Type I and local hypotheses; still a criterion, not arbitrary-data propagation
  + [source_002] is Geometry of turbulent dissipation and the Navier-Stokes regularity problem
    = link: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8065050/
    = use: geometric depletion is a serious regularity framework, but coherence of vorticity direction remains the kind of condition to control
  + [source_003] is Miller, The Navier-Stokes strain equation with applications to enstrophy growth and regularity
    = link: https://www.math.utoronto.ca/mccann/papers/MillerPhD19.pdf
    = use: strain/enstrophy identities expose alignment with strain eigenvectors and regularity criteria, but observed alignment is not a propagated global invariant
  + [source_004] is Beirao da Veiga and Berselli, Navier-Stokes equations: Some questions related to the direction of the vorticity
    = link: https://people.dm.unipi.it/beiraodaveiga/pdf/hbv-127.pdf
    = use: Holder regularity of vorticity direction can imply regularity, but the Holder condition remains assumed
  + [source_005] is Vasseur, Regularity criterion for 3D Navier-Stokes equations in terms of the direction of the velocity
    = link: https://web.ma.utexas.edu/users/vasseur/documents/preprints/NSdirection2.pdf
    = use: direction-based regularity criteria reinforce the source-document geometry reading while staying conditional

& [CandidateInvariantScan] is the bounded result
  + [candidate_001_vorticity_direction_modulus] is meaningful_but_conditional
    = role: coherence or continuity of vorticity direction can deplete vortex stretching
    = propagation_status: not derived for arbitrary smooth data
    = first_gap: no evolution inequality preserves the required modulus through possible singularity formation
  + [candidate_002_strain_eigenframe_alignment] is meaningful_but_heuristic_to_conditional
    = role: alignment with strain eigenvectors can rewrite or bound enstrophy growth terms
    = propagation_status: not a known monotone invariant in the current frame
    = first_gap: nonlinear strain evolution can amplify rather than dissipatively control the needed alignment
  + [candidate_003_scale_invariant_type_i_alignment] is special_conditional
    = role: scale-invariant alignment assumptions near possible singularities can exclude blowup in scoped settings
    = propagation_status: conditional under Type I or local assumptions
    = first_gap: Type I/alignment assumptions are not proved from arbitrary initial data
  + [candidate_004_velocity_direction_criteria] is direction_criterion
    = role: direction fields may encode regularity conditions
    = propagation_status: criterion only
    = first_gap: no source-derived flow law forces the direction condition

